rds, and this is why the book is aimed at a wider audience. Where special knowledge is required, the reader will find complete and easy-to-understand explanations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexForeign words and phrases. 4aEntlehnung. 4aFremdwort. 4aLinguistik. 4aMorphologie (Sprache). 4aOrthographie. 4aPhonologie. 4aPurismus (Sprache). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aBorrowing.  aLinguistics.  aLoan Word.  aMorphology (Language).  aOrthography.  aPhonology.  aPurism (Language).08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311028841440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028842140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110288421423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110288421/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014